IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: WOMENVENTURE IS DEDICATED TO HELPING WOMEN ATTAIN ECONOMIC SELF-SUFFICIENCY.
IRS990.MissionDesc: WOMENVENTURE HELPS WOMEN ATTAIN ECONOMIC SELF-SUFFICIENCY THROUGH THE CREATION AND GROWTH OF PROFITABLE AND SUSTAINABLE BUSINESSES.
IRS990.Desc: BUSINESS DEVELOPMENT:WOMENVENTURE SUPPORTS WOMEN TO ATTAIN ECONOMIC SUCCESS AND INDEPENDENCE BY PROVIDING TRAINING, CAPITAL, AND ONGOING CONSULTATION THROUGH ALL STAGES OF BUSINESS DEVELOPMENT. CAPITAL IS PROVIDED TO LOW-COLLATERAL, HIGHER RISK CLIENTS THROUGH FEDERAL, STATE, PRIVATE FOUNDATION, AND CITY FUNDS. WOMENVENTURE IS A U.S. SMALL BUSINESS ADMINISTRATION (SBA) MICROLOAN PROVIDER. QUALIFIED BORROWERS CAN RECEIVE START UP AND EXPANSION LOANS OF $500 - $50,000. WOMENVENTURE DISBURSED AND FACILITATED $4.9 MILLION IN LOANS HELPING 206 SMALL BUSINESSES. THIS HELPED CREATE OR RETAIN 916 JOBS. THE BUSINESS OWNERS PAID THEMSELVES AN AVERAGE WAGE OF $26 AN HOUR.WOMENVENTURE IS ALSO AN SBA WOMEN'S BUSINESS CENTER (WBC) THAT IS A PART OF A NATIONAL NETWORK OF NEARLY 100 EDUCATIONAL CENTERS DEDICATED TO ASSISTING WOMEN START AND GROW SMALL BUSINESSES. AS PART OF THE EDUCATIONAL CLASSES PROVIDED, WOMENVENTURE ALSO HELP CLIENTS NETWORK WITH OTHER ENTREPRENEURS AND MATCHES WOMEN WITH MENTORS TO ENSURE PROGRESS AND SUCCESS. IN TAX YEAR 2017, THE ORGANIZATION PROVIDED 9,662 HOURS OF TRAINING AND CONSULTING TO CLIENTS.THE ORGANIZATION PROVIDES TRAINING AND SERVICES (FREE AND PAID COURSES) TO HELP CLIENTS RECOGNIZE THEIR SKILLS AND PERSONAL IDEAS WHICH CAN BE TURNED INTO BUSINESSES BY HELPING THEM CREATE BUSINESS PLANS & LEARN ABOUT LEGAL COMPLIANCES, MARKETING, FINANCIAL, HUMAN RESOURCES, OPERATION AND SALES ASPECT OF THE BUSINESS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THIS IS A PERMANENT ENDOWMENT TO SUPPORT THE PROGRAMS OF WOMENVENTURE. INVESTMENT GAINS ON THE ENDOWMENT MAY BE USED TO CARRY OUT THE GENERAL CHARITABLE PURPOSE OF WOMENVENTURE.

WOMENVENTURE IS NOT CURRENTLY UNDER EXAMINATION BY ANY TAXING JURISDICTION. FEDERAL AND STATE TAX AUTHORITIES HAVE THE RIGHT TO EXAMINE THE CURRENT AND PRIOR THREE YEARS' RETURNS. ANY INTEREST OR PENALTIES ASSOCIATED WITH TAX POSITIONS ARE REPORTED AS SUCH WITHIN THE MANAGEMENT AND GENERAL EXPENSES CATEGORY. FOR THE YEAR ENDED JUNE 30, 2018 OR 2017, THERE WERE NO SUCH INTEREST OR PENALTIES RECORDED IN THE ACCOMPANYING FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION TRACKS THE NUMBER OF CONTRIBUTIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION WORKS CLOSELY WITH AN OUTSIDE PAID PREPARER WHO IS EXPERIENCED WITH FORM 990. THE ORGANIZATION'S CFO AND FINANCIAL MANAGER PROVIDE THE PREPARER WITH FULL INFORMATION AND CLOSELY REVIEW THE RETURN PRIOR TO GOING TO FINAL DRAFT. THE PAID PREPARER WALKS THROUGH THE 990 WITH THE FINANCE COMMITTEE AND TAKES QUESTIONS. THEREAFTER, THE FINANCE COMMITTEE APPROVES THE FORM, WITH MINOR CHANGES, AND RECOMMENDS TO THE BOARD FOR APPROVAL. THE BOARD REVIEWS AND APPROVES, AUTHORIZING THE CEO TO SIGN THE FORM.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD AND STAFF MAKE ANNUAL DECLARATIONS OF ANY CONFLICTS OF INTEREST. WHEN CONFLICTS ARISE DURING THE YEAR, THE INTERESTED PERSON IS TO REPORT THE CONFLICT TO THE BOARD CHAIR OR THE BOARD CHAIR'S DESIGNEE. THE BOARD CHAIR, OR THE BOARD CHAIR'S DESIGNEE, DECLARES IF IT IS IN FACT A CONFLICT. DURING THE DISCUSSION OF THE TRANSACTION OR AGREEMENT IN QUESTION, THE INTERESTED BOARD MEMBER IS REMOVED FROM THE ROOM. THAT BOARD MEMBER ALSO MUST ABSTAIN FROM VOTING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: WOMENVENTURE USES THE MINNESOTA COUNCIL OF NONPROFITS SALARY SURVEY WHEN DETERMINING COMPENSATION FOR TOP MANAGEMENT OFFICIALS AND KEY EMPLOYEES. THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR'S SALARY IS REVIEWED BY THE FULL BOARD ANNUALLY; THE BOARD CHAIR HAS A DIRECTIVE TO REVIEW MARKET COMPENSATION AND MAKE RECOMMENDATIONS. THE CFO'S COMPENSATION IS DETERMINED BY THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR BASED ON REVIEW OF MARKET COMPENSATION RATES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
